{
  "name": "Production Branch Protection - Organization Wide",
  "description": "Enterprise-wide ruleset enforcing security and compliance for production deployments across all 1000 repositories",
  "enforcement": "active",
  "target": "branch",
  "conditions": {
    "ref_name": {
      "include": [
        "refs/heads/main",
        "refs/heads/master",
        "refs/heads/production"
      ]
    }
  },
  "rules": [
    {
      "type": "pull_request",
      "parameters": {
        "required_approving_review_count": 2,
        "dismiss_stale_reviews_on_push": true,
        "require_code_owner_review": true,
        "require_last_push_approval": true,
        "required_review_thread_resolution": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "required_status_checks",
      "parameters": {
        "strict_required_status_checks_policy": true,
        "required_status_checks": [
          {
            "context": "Required Security Scan",
            "integration_id": 12345
          },
          {
            "context": "Required SBOM Generation",
            "integration_id": 12345
          },
          {
            "context": "Required Policy Validation",
            "integration_id": 12345
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "required_workflows",
      "parameters": {
        "required_workflows": [
          {
            "path": ".github/workflows/required-security.yml",
            "repository": "org-name/.github-private",
            "ref": "refs/heads/main"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "non_fast_forward",
      "parameters": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "commit_message_pattern",
      "parameters": {
        "operator": "regex",
        "pattern": "^(feat|fix|docs|chore|refactor|test)\\(.+\\):.+",
        "name": "Conventional Commits",
        "negate": false
      }
    }
  ],
  "bypass_actors": [
    {
      "actor_id": 1,
      "actor_type": "OrganizationAdmin",
      "bypass_mode": "always"
    }
  ]
}

/*
 * GitHub Enterprise Feature: Organization Rulesets
 * Purpose: Enforce policies across ALL repositories from one central location
 * Cost: Included in GitHub Enterprise Cloud
 *
 * How to Apply:
 * 1. Go to Organization Settings → Rules → Rulesets
 * 2. Create new ruleset
 * 3. Import this JSON configuration
 * 4. Applies to all current and future repos
 *
 * What This Provides:
 * ✅ Centralized policy management
 * ✅ Requires 2 approvals + code owner review
 * ✅ Enforces required status checks from Required Workflows
 * ✅ Prevents force pushes to main
 * ✅ Enforces commit message format
 *
 * What This DOESN'T Prevent:
 * ❌ Developer's workflow deploying before required workflow completes
 * ❌ Developer removing security jobs from their workflow
 * ❌ Subtle bypasses (continue-on-error, conditional skips)
 *
 * The Core Issue:
 *
 * This ruleset requires status checks from Required Workflows.
 * But it CANNOT enforce what happens in the developer's own workflow.
 *
 * Example:
 *
 * Required Workflow (org-wide):
 *   ├─ Scans filesystem with Trivy ✅
 *   └─ Creates status check "Required Security Scan" ✅
 *
 * Developer's Workflow (in their repo):
 *   ├─ Builds Docker image
 *   ├─ Skips image scan (removed from workflow)
 *   ├─ Deploys to production
 *   └─ Runs in PARALLEL with required workflow
 *
 * Result:
 *   ├─ Required workflow status check passes ✅
 *   ├─ Ruleset allows merge ✅
 *   └─ But Docker image was NEVER scanned ❌
 *
 * Why:
 *   - Required workflow scans source code (filesystem)
 *   - Developer's workflow builds image AFTER checkout
 *   - No mechanism to make deploy wait for required workflow
 *   - Both workflows run independently
 *
 * Timing Race Condition:
 *
 * t=0:    Developer pushes to PR
 * t=0:    Required workflow starts (filesystem scan)
 * t=0:    Developer's workflow starts (build + test)
 * t=3min: Developer's workflow completes ✅
 * t=5min: Required workflow finds CVE in dependency ❌
 *
 * Ruleset check:
 *   ✅ PR can be merged (required workflow created status)
 *   ✅ 2 approvals obtained
 *   ✅ All checks passed
 *
 * After merge:
 *   t=6min: Deploy workflow runs
 *   t=9min: Vulnerable code deployed to production ❌
 *
 * The required workflow found the CVE, but too late.
 *
 * Compare to Harness:
 *
 * In Harness, templates enforce sequential execution:
 *
 * template:
 *   stages:
 *     - stage:
 *         name: Security
 *         locked: true
 *         spec:
 *           scan:
 *             failOnCVE: true
 *             waitForResults: true  # ← Blocks next stage
 *     - stage:
 *         name: Deploy
 *         dependsOn: [Security]  # ← Cannot run until security passes
 *
 * Result: Deployment CANNOT happen until security scan passes.
 * This is architectural, not policy-based.
 */
